-1.title: The Makeover, Part 2 W/Damien Lemon

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

-1.plot: Scott's got more fun up his sleeve challenging Shaina, another unsuspecting stylist, to transform Kari from a fashion-challenged-Slut-Ho into a mom-pleasing-fashionista. Comedian Damien Lemon shares his own grooming tips and his vision for being eternally stylish.

1.title: General Genetalia Boredom

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

1.plot: Couple Francois and Keith are looking to spice up their sex life with a new addition, so Scott helps them find the perfect partner for the job(s). Eddie, a social worker by day, has no idea he's walking into a talk show set, but luckily he's not shy when it comes to talking about sex.

2.title: Bedtime with Vinny

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

2.plot: Rachel has no idea she's walking into a talk show where she'll compete to be in a threesome. The self-proclaimed sex addict says she'd rather make it a four-way and just get to it. Vinny Guadagnino shows up to talk sex terms and spills one of his celebrity hookups.

3.title: Slurp You Like Spaghetti

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

3.plot: The competition gets steamy when threesome candidates Eddie and Rachel get busy in bed in two final challenges to win a spot in a threesome with couple Keith and Francois. Vinny Guadagnino gives his thoughts on dog toys and golden vibrators in the bedroom.

4.title: How Did You Get My Photos?!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

4.plot: Sal Vulcano dishes about his hit TV show Impractical Jokers, slithery water slides and why he needs a Zen master. Dancer Katherine shows she's got the moves and attitude to handle any task thrown at her.

5.title: Diva Problems!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

5.plot: It's all Greek to Josh, the second ambushed assistant candidate, who immediately offers to quit when he meets his lovely competition. The two potential assistant rivals find a common ground when they eulogize "Fish," Sal's frozen fish.

6.title: Sal's Impractical Gauntlet

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

6.plot: The battle for the job hits the streets of New York City where Josh and Katherine face off in Sal's Assistant Gauntlet. Can they keep up with Sal's juicy demands, or will they quit before they're even hired?

7.title: What's in His Fanny Pack?

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

7.plot: Scott takes over Allison's art gallery with his talk show and interviews her date candidates, David and Mark, who have no idea what they're walking into. With some help from his Dad, Scott grills the guys about their love of cats and dirty fanny packs.

8.title: Blow the Comedian!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

8.plot: Scott surprises David and Mark with a special guest-comedian Jim Norton. Jim spills his own personal and truly shocking dating secret, then sizes up Allison's potential mates by roasting their dating app profile pics.

9.title: Slide Your Fingers Where?

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

9.plot: Things get even more personal with Jim Norton as candidates David and Mark face off in a sketchy competition to win over gallery owner Allison; but, she's leaving the final decision up to her dog.

10.title: My Dad Is My Roommate

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

10.plot: First candidate, Anthony, is shocked when he arrives at the loft and walks into Scott's talk show. Anthony is grilled about living with his dad in Staten Island, and his knowledge of roommate sex etiquette is put to the test.

11.title: Tawkwafina

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

11.plot: Julia smells something fishy when she shows up to check out the apartment. Scott challenges her to roll with everything to win over her potential roommates. Then, Scott takes over Awkwafina's Twitter account and posts some scandalous tweets.

12.title: Munchie Cook Off!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

12.plot: The two candidates cook up munchie feasts to satisfy their potential roommates' post-toke cravings. And Awkwafina reveals that these crazy culinary concoctions aren't the weirdest thing she's ever eaten (to say the least).

13.title: Meet the Director!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

13.plot: Scott meets filmmaker Raf, who lives and makes movies in his parents' basement with his old-bearded buddy Moose. Scott helps Raf cast the perfect actress for his new film World Domination. The first actress thinks it's a regular audition, but gets a huge shock when she walks into a talk show set. The surprises don't stop there.

The first actress thinks it's a regular audition, but gets a huge shock when she walks into a talk show set. The surprises don't stop there.

15.title: World Domination Challenge

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

15.plot: They all head down to Raf's basement for the final screen test. The tension mounts to determine which actress has what it takes to land the role of a lifetime, but not before leading man Moose needs a bathroom break.

16.title: Show Me Your Stankface

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

16.plot: Siberian Death March's lead singer Michael shares the two basic requirements to be in his band: show up and play fast. First contender, Will, is surprised by Scott's talk show and his bass 'stankface' knowledge is put to the test.

17.title: Big Jay Uncorks!

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

17.plot: Another potential bass player, Kenny, arrives in style and the competition heats up when he freestyles some rhymes. Big Jay Oakerson unleashes hysterical jabs at the Start Talkin' crew and confesses a shameful mistake he made as a teenager with a writing utensil.

18.title: Who's Got More Balls?

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

18.plot: In death metal you need to be ready for any scenario thrown at you on stage...literally. So, for Will and Kenny it's anyone's game as they slap the bass while dodging balls being hurled at them by Scott and Big Jay.

19.title: Bouncer Battle W/Guys We F@#Ked: Part 1

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

19.plot: Celebrity chef Jordan Andino dishes on cooking for his celeb clients with famous booties. His new club needs their own big-ass bouncer for when the drinks start pouring at night. Goldwyn, the first unsuspecting bouncer candidate, is shocked, but at 6'10", 300lbs, he is totally up for anything.

20.title: Bouncer Battle W/Guys We F@#Ked: Part 2

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

20.plot: The competition grows when the other bouncer hopeful Steve arrives. The two giants get a little surprise from podcast stars Corinne and Krystyna who divulge their deepest darkest sexual encounters, and Scott spills the beans on thinking sex is "dumb."

21.title: Bouncer Battle W/Guys We F@#Ked: Part 3

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

21.plot: The guys go head-to-head in their biggest challenge yet...to keep rowdy drunk girls-played by Corinne and Krystyna-on the other side of the velvet rope. Will these sweet and sour talking ladies wiggle their way past the burly bouncers?

22.title: The Makeover, Part 1 W/Damien Lemon

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

22.plot: Kari's mom has A LOT to say about what's wrong with her daughter's overly slutty look. Scott surprises top NYC stylist Marcelo Gaia by making him a guest on his talk show and puts his skillful hands to the test.

23.title: The Makeover, Part 3 W/Damien Lemon

episode of.title: Start Talkin' with Scott Rogowsky (TV Series 2017– )

23.plot: Scott and Damien hit the sidewalks of NYC where they ambush two street vendors with a 5-minute makeover. Can the stylists make these regular peeps off the street red carpet ready and win Kari's trust? Or will she look like a slut-ho forever-mo?
